parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations, especially when the vehicle surges forward at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently
engine RPMs increase without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle surges forward
the brakes vibrate when applied
the throttle gets stuck
and the vehicle accelerates even when the accelerator pedal is not depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck throttle or failed cruise control cable can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The throttle gets stuck
the cruise control cable breaks or fractures
the engine RPMs increase without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates independently
and the brakes vibrate when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed speed control cable can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The speed control cable breaks or fails
the engine RPMs increase without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates independently
and the brakes vibrate when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal switch can cause the vehicle to not come out of park, and the brake lights may not operate, leading to potential accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle will not come out of park
the brake lights do not operate when the pedal is depressed
the brake lights stay on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents or safety risks, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to accelerate or move
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slippage of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to potential accidents or safety risks, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
especially when shifting into reverse
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents or safety risks, especially if it occurs while parking or in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle jumps forward or moves unexpectedly
especially when starting or idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop lamp switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to inability to shift the vehicle from park to drive, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on all the time or do not come on at all
inability to shift the vehicle from park to drive
brake lights do not work while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Vehicle speeds up when braking
requiring sudden and hard braking to avoid accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to shake or vibrate when braking, leading to reduced control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
warped brake rotors.
